31/10/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Foreign Minister Razvan Ungureanu said on Sunday (30 October) that the government has launched an investigation into possible abuse of the UN oil-for food programme by Romanian firms. 
According to local media, 11 companies may have paid kickbacks to Saddam Hussein's regime to gain access to Iraqi oil.
In other news, Ungureanu is in New York for the UN Security Council session. 
He is expected to meet with US counterpart Condoleezza Rice. 
(Nine o'clock, Rompres - 31/10/05; AFP - 30/10/05)
